Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand   trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok. Thai
financial markets will be closed tomorrow and April 16 for
public holidays.  The  SET Index (SET)  rose 1.3 percent to 1,169.45, the most since
March 27, snapping a four-day decline.  Sugar producers:  Khon Kaen Sugar Industry Pcl (KSL)  
climbed 1.5 percent to 13.50 baht, halting a five-day slide.
 Khonburi Sugar Pcl (KBS)   gained 2 percent to 10.30 baht, its
biggest increase since Feb. 17.  Sugar production may climb to a record for a second year,
according to Thailandâ€™s Office of the Cane & Sugar Board.  Tourism-related companies:  Airports of Thailand Pcl  (AOT
TB) added 1.8 percent to 58 baht.  Minor International Pcl (MINT)   increased 1.6 percent to 12.70 baht, the most in two weeks.
  Laguna Resorts & Hotels Pcl (LRH)   advanced 3.1 percent to
41.25 baht, the largest gain since Nov. 21.  Thai Airways
International Pcl (THAI)   rose 3.2 percent to 25.50 baht.  An 8.6-magnitude earthquake struck off the coast of
 Indonesia  yesterday, triggering tsunami warnings in countries
including Thailand. The warnings were lifted and no casualties
were reported from the quake.  To contact the reporter on this story:
